istance to cadets who without such aid would be unable to attend and to provide aid to cadets with superior academic abilities  Merit based scholarships are administered by the Dean s Office and have different deadlines  Contact the Dean s Office at  540 464 7212 or for more information go to http www vmi edu Content aspx id 10737424062   We are here to help find the best solution for you  your situation  and your needs  Please contact our office if you have any questions  at  540  464 7208  General Notices  FAFSA Changes for 2017 2018   New Federal Student Aid  FSA  Identification to Replace the PIN Deadlines  March 1st New Cadets April 1st Returning Cadets Resources All new and returning cadets must complete two forms to receive Financial Aid  VMI Financial Aid Application FAFSA   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 